https://schema.org/duringMedia.name: duringMedia
https://schema.org/duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

https://schema.org/nonprofitStatus.name: nonprofitStatus
https://schema.org/nonprofitStatus.description: nonprofit Status indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

https://schema.org/alcoholWarning.name: alcoholWarning
https://schema.org/alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

https://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.name: hasCourseInstance
https://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.description: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

https://schema.org/possibleComplication.name: possibleComplication
https://schema.org/possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

https://schema.org/legislationApplies.name: legislationApplies
https://schema.org/legislationApplies.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

https://schema.org/instructor.name: instructor
https://schema.org/instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

https://schema.org/distance.name: distance
https://schema.org/distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

https://schema.org/jobLocationType.name: jobLocationType
https://schema.org/jobLocationType.description: A description of the job location (e.g TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

https://schema.org/softwareAddOn.name: softwareAddOn
https://schema.org/softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

https://schema.org/prescribingInfo.name: prescribingInfo
https://schema.org/prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

https://schema.org/hasOccupation.name: hasOccupation
https://schema.org/hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

https://schema.org/occupationalCredentia.name: occupationalCredentialAwarded
https://schema.org/occupationalCredentia.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

https://schema.org/emissionsCO2.name: emissionsCO2
https://schema.org/emissionsCO2.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

https://schema.org/bccRecipient.name: bccRecipient
https://schema.org/bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

https://schema.org/departurePlatform.name: departurePlatform
https://schema.org/departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

https://schema.org/interactingDrug.name: interactingDrug
https://schema.org/interactingDrug.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

https://schema.org/credentialCategory.name: credentialCategory
https://schema.org/credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

https://schema.org/courseMode.name: courseMode
https://schema.org/courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

https://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.name: includedDataCatalog
https://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

https://schema.org/bodyLocation.name: bodyLocation
https://schema.org/bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

https://schema.org/maintainer.name: maintainer
https://schema.org/maintainer.description: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always  possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The [[isBasedOn]] property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.

https://schema.org/locationCreated.name: locationCreated
https://schema.org/locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/contentLocation.name: contentLocation
https://schema.org/contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

https://schema.org/vehicleEngine.name: vehicleEngine
https://schema.org/vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

https://schema.org/isInvolvedInBiologica.name: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
https://schema.org/isInvolvedInBiologica.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

https://schema.org/releasedEvent.name: releasedEvent
https://schema.org/releasedEvent.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

https://schema.org/measuredProperty.name: measuredProperty
https://schema.org/measuredProperty.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], either a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

https://schema.org/programType.name: programType
https://schema.org/programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc..

https://schema.org/publication.name: publication
https://schema.org/publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

https://schema.org/associatedPathophysio.name: associatedPathophysiology
https://schema.org/associatedPathophysio.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

https://schema.org/sku.name: sku
https://schema.org/sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

https://schema.org/serviceLocation.name: serviceLocation
https://schema.org/serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

https://schema.org/industry.name: industry
https://schema.org/industry.description: The industry associated with the job position.

https://schema.org/item.name: item
https://schema.org/item.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists')’.

https://schema.org/educationalLevel.name: educationalLevel
https://schema.org/educationalLevel.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

https://schema.org/monthlyMinimumRepayme.name: monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
https://schema.org/monthlyMinimumRepayme.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

https://schema.org/mainEntity.name: mainEntity
https://schema.org/mainEntity.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/numberOfFullBathrooms.name: numberOfFullBathrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfFullBathrooms.description: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

https://schema.org/subEvents.name: subEvents
https://schema.org/subEvents.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

https://schema.org/musicGroupMember.name: musicGroupMember
https://schema.org/musicGroupMember.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

https://schema.org/ownedThrough.name: ownedThrough
https://schema.org/ownedThrough.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

https://schema.org/jobBenefits.name: jobBenefits
https://schema.org/jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

https://schema.org/serialNumber.name: serialNumber
https://schema.org/serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

https://schema.org/serviceArea.name: serviceArea
https://schema.org/serviceArea.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

https://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.name: entertainmentBusiness
https://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

https://schema.org/preparation.name: preparation
https://schema.org/preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

https://schema.org/bioChemSimilarity.name: bioChemSimilarity
https://schema.org/bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

https://schema.org/trailerWeight.name: trailerWeight
https://schema.org/trailerWeight.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/holdingArchive.name: holdingArchive
https://schema.org/holdingArchive.description: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

https://schema.org/requiredMaxAge.name: requiredMaxAge
https://schema.org/requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

https://schema.org/prepTime.name: prepTime
https://schema.org/prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/steps.name: steps
https://schema.org/steps.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

https://schema.org/educationalFramework.name: educationalFramework
https://schema.org/educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

https://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyVal.name: broadcastFrequencyValue
https://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyVal.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

https://schema.org/hoursAvailable.name: hoursAvailable
https://schema.org/hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

https://schema.org/maximumVirtualAttende.name: maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumVirtualAttende.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

https://schema.org/startTime.name: startTime
https://schema.org/startTime.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

https://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.name: encodesCreativeWork
https://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

https://schema.org/reportNumber.name: reportNumber
https://schema.org/reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

https://schema.org/datasetTimeInterval.name: datasetTimeInterval
https://schema.org/datasetTimeInterval.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

https://schema.org/startDate.name: startDate
https://schema.org/startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

https://schema.org/unitText.name: unitText
https://schema.org/unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

https://schema.org/valueName.name: valueName
https://schema.org/valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

https://schema.org/educationRequirements.name: educationRequirements
https://schema.org/educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

https://schema.org/currenciesAccepted.name: currenciesAccepted
https://schema.org/currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/dateReceived.name: dateReceived
https://schema.org/dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

https://schema.org/keywords.name: keywords
https://schema.org/keywords.description: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

https://schema.org/availableThrough.name: availableThrough
https://schema.org/availableThrough.description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

https://schema.org/worstRating.name: worstRating
https://schema.org/worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

https://schema.org/restPeriods.name: restPeriods
https://schema.org/restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

https://schema.org/requiredCollateral.name: requiredCollateral
https://schema.org/requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

https://schema.org/hasBioChemEntityPart.name: hasBioChemEntityPart
https://schema.org/hasBioChemEntityPart.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

https://schema.org/isConsumableFor.name: isConsumableFor
https://schema.org/isConsumableFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

https://schema.org/sourcedFrom.name: sourcedFrom
https://schema.org/sourcedFrom.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

https://schema.org/cvdNumBeds.name: cvdNumBeds
https://schema.org/cvdNumBeds.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

https://schema.org/acquiredFrom.name: acquiredFrom
https://schema.org/acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

https://schema.org/maximumAttendeeCapaci.name: maximumAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumAttendeeCapaci.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

https://schema.org/webFeed.name: webFeed
https://schema.org/webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.name: healthPlanCopayOption
https://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.description: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

https://schema.org/hasDefinedTerm.name: hasDefinedTerm
https://schema.org/hasDefinedTerm.description: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

https://schema.org/eligibilityToWorkRequ.name: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
https://schema.org/eligibilityToWorkRequ.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

https://schema.org/inker.name: inker
https://schema.org/inker.description: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

https://schema.org/hasMap.name: hasMap
https://schema.org/hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/ownedFrom.name: ownedFrom
https://schema.org/ownedFrom.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

https://schema.org/targetDescription.name: targetDescription
https://schema.org/targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/menuAddOn.name: menuAddOn
https://schema.org/menuAddOn.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

https://schema.org/accountId.name: accountId
https://schema.org/accountId.description: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

https://schema.org/readonlyValue.name: readonlyValue
https://schema.org/readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

https://schema.org/paymentDueDate.name: paymentDueDate
https://schema.org/paymentDueDate.description: The date that payment is due.

https://schema.org/departureStation.name: departureStation
https://schema.org/departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

https://schema.org/issueNumber.name: issueNumber
https://schema.org/issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

https://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.name: hospitalAffiliation
https://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.description: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

https://schema.org/epidemiology.name: epidemiology
https://schema.org/epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

https://schema.org/editEIDR.name: editEIDR
https://schema.org/editEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J", has several edits e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

https://schema.org/dateIssued.name: dateIssued
https://schema.org/dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

https://schema.org/archivedAt.name: archivedAt
https://schema.org/archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

https://schema.org/reviewBody.name: reviewBody
https://schema.org/reviewBody.description: The actual body of the review.

https://schema.org/transitTimeLabel.name: transitTimeLabel
https://schema.org/transitTimeLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

https://schema.org/geoCovers.name: geoCovers
https://schema.org/geoCovers.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/identifyingTest.name: identifyingTest
https://schema.org/identifyingTest.description: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

https://schema.org/validIn.name: validIn
https://schema.org/validIn.description: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

https://schema.org/floorSize.name: floorSize
https://schema.org/floorSize.description:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

https://schema.org/season.name: season
https://schema.org/season.description: A season in a media series.

https://schema.org/permitAudience.name: permitAudience
https://schema.org/permitAudience.description: The target audience for this permit.

https://schema.org/boardingPolicy.name: boardingPolicy
https://schema.org/boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

https://schema.org/seatingCapacity.name: seatingCapacity
https://schema.org/seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons

https://schema.org/pageStart.name: pageStart
https://schema.org/pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

https://schema.org/targetUrl.name: targetUrl
https://schema.org/targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/minPrice.name: minPrice
https://schema.org/minPrice.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

https://schema.org/position.name: position
https://schema.org/position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

https://schema.org/countriesSupported.name: countriesSupported
https://schema.org/countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

https://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.name: accessibilityAPI
https://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API ([WebSchemas wiki lists possible values](http://www.w3.org/wiki/WebSchemas/Accessibility)).

https://schema.org/encoding.name: encoding
https://schema.org/encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

https://schema.org/educationalProgramMod.name: educationalProgramMode
https://schema.org/educationalProgramMod.description: Similar to courseMode, The medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

https://schema.org/securityClearanceRequ.name: securityClearanceRequirement
https://schema.org/securityClearanceRequ.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

https://schema.org/availableLanguage.name: availableLanguage
https://schema.org/availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]]

https://schema.org/areaServed.name: areaServed
https://schema.org/areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

https://schema.org/financialAidEligible.name: financialAidEligible
https://schema.org/financialAidEligible.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

https://schema.org/diseaseSpreadStatisti.name: diseaseSpreadStatistics
https://schema.org/diseaseSpreadStatisti.description:
Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or
  described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is
  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

https://schema.org/inChIKey.name: inChIKey
https://schema.org/inChIKey.description: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

https://schema.org/makesOffer.name: makesOffer
https://schema.org/makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

https://schema.org/artMedium.name: artMedium
https://schema.org/artMedium.description: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

https://schema.org/currency.name: currency
https://schema.org/currency.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/diversityPolicy.name: diversityPolicy
https://schema.org/diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

https://schema.org/relatedDrug.name: relatedDrug
https://schema.org/relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

https://schema.org/isRelatedTo.name: isRelatedTo
https://schema.org/isRelatedTo.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

https://schema.org/requirements.name: requirements
https://schema.org/requirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

https://schema.org/typicalTest.name: typicalTest
https://schema.org/typicalTest.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

https://schema.org/functionalClass.name: functionalClass
https://schema.org/functionalClass.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

https://schema.org/printColumn.name: printColumn
https://schema.org/printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

https://schema.org/eligibleCustomerType.name: eligibleCustomerType
https://schema.org/eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

https://schema.org/inPlaylist.name: inPlaylist
https://schema.org/inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

https://schema.org/answerExplanation.name: answerExplanation
https://schema.org/answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

https://schema.org/gettingTestedInfo.name: gettingTestedInfo
https://schema.org/gettingTestedInfo.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/smokingAllowed.name: smokingAllowed
https://schema.org/smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

https://schema.org/backstory.name: backstory
https://schema.org/backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

https://schema.org/studyLocation.name: studyLocation
https://schema.org/studyLocation.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

https://schema.org/adverseOutcome.name: adverseOutcome
https://schema.org/adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

https://schema.org/provider.name: provider
https://schema.org/provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

https://schema.org/hostingOrganization.name: hostingOrganization
https://schema.org/hostingOrganization.description: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

https://schema.org/costCategory.name: costCategory
https://schema.org/costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

https://schema.org/termsPerYear.name: termsPerYear
https://schema.org/termsPerYear.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

https://schema.org/reservationId.name: reservationId
https://schema.org/reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

https://schema.org/branch.name: branch
https://schema.org/branch.description: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

https://schema.org/returnFees.name: returnFees
https://schema.org/returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason)

https://schema.org/trainNumber.name: trainNumber
https://schema.org/trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

https://schema.org/transcript.name: transcript
https://schema.org/transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

https://schema.org/followup.name: followup
https://schema.org/followup.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

https://schema.org/episodes.name: episodes
https://schema.org/episodes.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

https://schema.org/callSign.name: callSign
https://schema.org/callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

https://schema.org/dateDeleted.name: dateDeleted
https://schema.org/dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

https://schema.org/editor.name: editor
https://schema.org/editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/isPlanForApartment.name: isPlanForApartment
https://schema.org/isPlanForApartment.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

https://schema.org/arrivalBoatTerminal.name: arrivalBoatTerminal
https://schema.org/arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

https://schema.org/travelBans.name: travelBans
https://schema.org/travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/identifier.name: identifier
https://schema.org/identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

https://schema.org/sdLicense.name: sdLicense
https://schema.org/sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

https://schema.org/actionStatus.name: actionStatus
https://schema.org/actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

https://schema.org/doesNotShip.name: doesNotShip
https://schema.org/doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

https://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.name: ineligibleRegion
https://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

https://schema.org/urlTemplate.name: urlTemplate
https://schema.org/urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

https://schema.org/reviewRating.name: reviewRating
https://schema.org/reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

https://schema.org/hasVariant.name: hasVariant
https://schema.org/hasVariant.description: Indicates a [[Product]] that is a member of this [[ProductGroup]] (or [[ProductModel]]).

https://schema.org/isrcCode.name: isrcCode
https://schema.org/isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

https://schema.org/strengthValue.name: strengthValue
https://schema.org/strengthValue.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

https://schema.org/polygon.name: polygon
https://schema.org/polygon.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

https://schema.org/usageInfo.name: usageInfo
https://schema.org/usageInfo.description:
The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.

This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

https://schema.org/legislationTransposes.name: legislationTransposes
https://schema.org/legislationTransposes.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

https://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.name: expectedArrivalFrom
https://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

https://schema.org/referencesOrder.name: referencesOrder
https://schema.org/referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

https://schema.org/aggregateRating.name: aggregateRating
https://schema.org/aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

https://schema.org/recognizingAuthority.name: recognizingAuthority
https://schema.org/recognizingAuthority.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

https://schema.org/monoisotopicMolecular.name: monoisotopicMolecularWeight
https://schema.org/monoisotopicMolecular.description: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OFMechVentPa.name: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OFMechVentPa.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

https://schema.org/yearBuilt.name: yearBuilt
https://schema.org/yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

https://schema.org/validUntil.name: validUntil
https://schema.org/validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

https://schema.org/billingPeriod.name: billingPeriod
https://schema.org/billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

https://schema.org/cssSelector.name: cssSelector
https://schema.org/cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

https://schema.org/subStructure.name: subStructure
https://schema.org/subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

https://schema.org/availableOnDevice.name: availableOnDevice
https://schema.org/availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

https://schema.org/breadcrumb.name: breadcrumb
https://schema.org/breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

https://schema.org/artworkSurface.name: artworkSurface
https://schema.org/artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

https://schema.org/exampleOfWork.name: exampleOfWork
https://schema.org/exampleOfWork.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.name: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

https://schema.org/contentReferenceTime.name: contentReferenceTime
https://schema.org/contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

https://schema.org/shippingSettingsLink.name: shippingSettingsLink
https://schema.org/shippingSettingsLink.description: Link to a page containing [[ShippingRateSettings]] and [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] details.

https://schema.org/iataCode.name: iataCode
https://schema.org/iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

https://schema.org/tocContinuation.name: tocContinuation
https://schema.org/tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

https://schema.org/causeOf.name: causeOf
https://schema.org/causeOf.description: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

https://schema.org/cutoffTime.name: cutoffTime
https://schema.org/cutoffTime.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

https://schema.org/isPartOf.name: isPartOf
https://schema.org/isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

https://schema.org/alternativeOf.name: alternativeOf
https://schema.org/alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19Died.name: cvdNumC19Died
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

https://schema.org/numberOfPages.name: numberOfPages
https://schema.org/numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

https://schema.org/performers.name: performers
https://schema.org/performers.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

https://schema.org/courseCode.name: courseCode
https://schema.org/courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

https://schema.org/gracePeriod.name: gracePeriod
https://schema.org/gracePeriod.description: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

https://schema.org/unitCode.name: unitCode
https://schema.org/unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

https://schema.org/riskFactor.name: riskFactor
https://schema.org/riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

https://schema.org/ticketToken.name: ticketToken
https://schema.org/ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

https://schema.org/trackingUrl.name: trackingUrl
https://schema.org/trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

https://schema.org/duration.name: duration
https://schema.org/duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/fuelType.name: fuelType
https://schema.org/fuelType.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

https://schema.org/sponsor.name: sponsor
https://schema.org/sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

https://schema.org/availabilityEnds.name: availabilityEnds
https://schema.org/availabilityEnds.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

https://schema.org/openingHours.name: openingHours
https://schema.org/openingHours.description: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

https://schema.org/valueAddedTaxIncluded.name: valueAddedTaxIncluded
https://schema.org/valueAddedTaxIncluded.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

https://schema.org/healthCondition.name: healthCondition
https://schema.org/healthCondition.description: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

https://schema.org/nutrition.name: nutrition
https://schema.org/nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

https://schema.org/inCodeSet.name: inCodeSet
https://schema.org/inCodeSet.description: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.

https://schema.org/contactOption.name: contactOption
https://schema.org/contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

https://schema.org/alignmentType.name: alignmentType
https://schema.org/alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

https://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.name: alternativeHeadline
https://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/variantCover.name: variantCover
https://schema.org/variantCover.description:
A description of the variant cover
    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch
    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnLabel.name: itemDefectReturnLabelSource
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnLabel.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

https://schema.org/executableLibraryName.name: executableLibraryName
https://schema.org/executableLibraryName.description: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

https://schema.org/roleName.name: roleName
https://schema.org/roleName.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

https://schema.org/discusses.name: discusses
https://schema.org/discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

https://schema.org/geoMidpoint.name: geoMidpoint
https://schema.org/geoMidpoint.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

https://schema.org/recommendedIntake.name: recommendedIntake
https://schema.org/recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

https://schema.org/gameServer.name: gameServer
https://schema.org/gameServer.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

https://schema.org/validFor.name: validFor
https://schema.org/validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

https://schema.org/geoDisjoint.name: geoDisjoint
https://schema.org/geoDisjoint.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM))

https://schema.org/arrivalStation.name: arrivalStation
https://schema.org/arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

https://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.name: associatedAnatomy
https://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

https://schema.org/originalMediaContextD.name: originalMediaContextDescription
https://schema.org/originalMediaContextD.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

https://schema.org/nextItem.name: nextItem
https://schema.org/nextItem.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

https://schema.org/healthcareReportingDa.name: healthcareReportingData
https://schema.org/healthcareReportingDa.description: Indicates data describing a hospital, e.g. a CDC [[CDCPMDRecord]] or as some kind of [[Dataset]].

https://schema.org/secondaryPrevention.name: secondaryPrevention
https://schema.org/secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

https://schema.org/runtimePlatform.name: runtimePlatform
https://schema.org/runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0).

https://schema.org/successorOf.name: successorOf
https://schema.org/successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

https://schema.org/busNumber.name: busNumber
https://schema.org/busNumber.description: The unique identifier for the bus.

https://schema.org/estimatedCost.name: estimatedCost
https://schema.org/estimatedCost.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

https://schema.org/gender.name: gender
https://schema.org/gender.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

https://schema.org/musicCompositionForm.name: musicCompositionForm
https://schema.org/musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

https://schema.org/confirmationNumber.name: confirmationNumber
https://schema.org/confirmationNumber.description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

https://schema.org/contactPoint.name: contactPoint
https://schema.org/contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

https://schema.org/startOffset.name: startOffset
https://schema.org/startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

https://schema.org/composer.name: composer
https://schema.org/composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

https://schema.org/targetPopulation.name: targetPopulation
https://schema.org/targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

https://schema.org/competencyRequired.name: competencyRequired
https://schema.org/competencyRequired.description: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

https://schema.org/replacer.name: replacer
https://schema.org/replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

https://schema.org/activityDuration.name: activityDuration
https://schema.org/activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

https://schema.org/measurementTechnique.name: measurementTechnique
https://schema.org/measurementTechnique.description:
A technique or technology used in a [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]),
corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using [[variableMeasured]]). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]].

https://schema.org/translator.name: translator
https://schema.org/translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

https://schema.org/legislationDate.name: legislationDate
https://schema.org/legislationDate.description: The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

https://schema.org/servingSize.name: servingSize
https://schema.org/servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

https://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.name: broadcastDisplayName
https://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

https://schema.org/transFatContent.name: transFatContent
https://schema.org/transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

https://schema.org/departureAirport.name: departureAirport
https://schema.org/departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

https://schema.org/isSimilarTo.name: isSimilarTo
https://schema.org/isSimilarTo.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

https://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.name: includedRiskFactor
https://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

https://schema.org/previousStartDate.name: previousStartDate
https://schema.org/previousStartDate.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

https://schema.org/recipient.name: recipient
https://schema.org/recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

https://schema.org/borrower.name: borrower
https://schema.org/borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

https://schema.org/vehicleConfiguration.name: vehicleConfiguration
https://schema.org/vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

https://schema.org/warrantyScope.name: warrantyScope
https://schema.org/warrantyScope.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

https://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.name: isAccessibleForFree
https://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

https://schema.org/numConstraints.name: numConstraints
https://schema.org/numConstraints.description: Indicates the number of constraints (not counting [[populationType]]) defined for a particular [[StatisticalPopulation]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalPopulation]].

https://schema.org/nonProprietaryName.name: nonProprietaryName
https://schema.org/nonProprietaryName.description: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

https://schema.org/sensoryRequirement.name: sensoryRequirement
https://schema.org/sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

https://schema.org/workLocation.name: workLocation
https://schema.org/workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

https://schema.org/programmingModel.name: programmingModel
https://schema.org/programmingModel.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

https://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.name: arrivalTerminal
https://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

https://schema.org/targetPlatform.name: targetPlatform
https://schema.org/targetPlatform.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

https://schema.org/contactPoints.name: contactPoints
https://schema.org/contactPoints.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

https://schema.org/suggestedAge.name: suggestedAge
https://schema.org/suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.name: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

https://schema.org/availableTest.name: availableTest
https://schema.org/availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

https://schema.org/significantLink.name: significantLink
https://schema.org/significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

https://schema.org/isProprietary.name: isProprietary
https://schema.org/isProprietary.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

https://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.name: broadcastTimezone
https://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts

https://schema.org/dependencies.name: dependencies
https://schema.org/dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

https://schema.org/workPresented.name: workPresented
https://schema.org/workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

https://schema.org/directors.name: directors
https://schema.org/directors.description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/musicalKey.name: musicalKey
https://schema.org/musicalKey.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

https://schema.org/prescriptionStatus.name: prescriptionStatus
https://schema.org/prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription eg. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

https://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePar.name: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
https://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePar.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

https://schema.org/disambiguatingDescrip.name: disambiguatingDescription
https://schema.org/disambiguatingDescrip.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

https://schema.org/normalRange.name: normalRange
https://schema.org/normalRange.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

https://schema.org/mainEntityOfPage.name: mainEntityOfPage
https://schema.org/mainEntityOfPage.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

https://schema.org/jurisdiction.name: jurisdiction
https://schema.org/jurisdiction.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

https://schema.org/relatedLink.name: relatedLink
https://schema.org/relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

https://schema.org/hasMenuItem.name: hasMenuItem
https://schema.org/hasMenuItem.description: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

https://schema.org/speechToTextMarkup.name: speechToTextMarkup
https://schema.org/speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

https://schema.org/handlingTime.name: handlingTime
https://schema.org/handlingTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

https://schema.org/produces.name: produces
https://schema.org/produces.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

https://schema.org/currentExchangeRate.name: currentExchangeRate
https://schema.org/currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

https://schema.org/suggestedGender.name: suggestedGender
https://schema.org/suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

https://schema.org/touristType.name: touristType
https://schema.org/touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. eg. Children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

https://schema.org/caption.name: caption
https://schema.org/caption.description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

https://schema.org/about.name: about
https://schema.org/about.description: The subject matter of the content.

https://schema.org/employmentType.name: employmentType
https://schema.org/employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

https://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.name: greaterOrEqual
https://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

https://schema.org/map.name: map
https://schema.org/map.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.name: broadcastServiceTier
https://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

https://schema.org/associatedDisease.name: associatedDisease
https://schema.org/associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

https://schema.org/billingAddress.name: billingAddress
https://schema.org/billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

https://schema.org/educationalAlignment.name: educationalAlignment
https://schema.org/educationalAlignment.description:
An alignment to an established educational framework.

This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

https://schema.org/license.name: license
https://schema.org/license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

https://schema.org/scheduledTime.name: scheduledTime
https://schema.org/scheduledTime.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

https://schema.org/characterAttribute.name: characterAttribute
https://schema.org/characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

https://schema.org/numberOfEpisodes.name: numberOfEpisodes
https://schema.org/numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

https://schema.org/endTime.name: endTime
https://schema.org/endTime.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

https://schema.org/isEncodedByBioChemEnt.name: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/isEncodedByBioChemEnt.description: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

https://schema.org/circle.name: circle
https://schema.org/circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

https://schema.org/grantee.name: grantee
https://schema.org/grantee.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

https://schema.org/phoneticText.name: phoneticText
https://schema.org/phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

https://schema.org/embedUrl.name: embedUrl
https://schema.org/embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

https://schema.org/flightNumber.name: flightNumber
https://schema.org/flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.name: healthPlanCostSharing
https://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.description: Whether The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

https://schema.org/byArtist.name: byArtist
https://schema.org/byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

https://schema.org/numberOfForwardGears.name: numberOfForwardGears
https://schema.org/numberOfForwardGears.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

https://schema.org/qualifications.name: qualifications
https://schema.org/qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

https://schema.org/itemReviewed.name: itemReviewed
https://schema.org/itemReviewed.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

https://schema.org/sharedContent.name: sharedContent
https://schema.org/sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

https://schema.org/seasonNumber.name: seasonNumber
https://schema.org/seasonNumber.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

https://schema.org/studySubject.name: studySubject
https://schema.org/studySubject.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

https://schema.org/toRecipient.name: toRecipient
https://schema.org/toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

https://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMetho.name: appliesToPaymentMethod
https://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMetho.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

https://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.name: ethicsPolicy
https://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

https://schema.org/costOrigin.name: costOrigin
https://schema.org/costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

https://schema.org/correctionsPolicy.name: correctionsPolicy
https://schema.org/correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

https://schema.org/recordedAt.name: recordedAt
https://schema.org/recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

https://schema.org/suggestedMaxAge.name: suggestedMaxAge
https://schema.org/suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

https://schema.org/encodingFormat.name: encodingFormat
https://schema.org/encodingFormat.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

https://schema.org/servicePostalAddress.name: servicePostalAddress
https://schema.org/servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

https://schema.org/businessFunction.name: businessFunction
https://schema.org/businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorColor.name: vehicleInteriorColor
https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

https://schema.org/offerCount.name: offerCount
https://schema.org/offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

https://schema.org/eduQuestionType.name: eduQuestionType
https://schema.org/eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

https://schema.org/expressedIn.name: expressedIn
https://schema.org/expressedIn.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

https://schema.org/engineType.name: engineType
https://schema.org/engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

https://schema.org/physiologicalBenefits.name: physiologicalBenefits
https://schema.org/physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

https://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.name: knownVehicleDamages
https://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

https://schema.org/ccRecipient.name: ccRecipient
https://schema.org/ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

https://schema.org/occupationalCategory.name: occupationalCategory
https://schema.org/occupationalCategory.description:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

https://schema.org/endOffset.name: endOffset
https://schema.org/endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

https://schema.org/pattern.name: pattern
https://schema.org/pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

https://schema.org/legislationConsolidat.name: legislationConsolidates
https://schema.org/legislationConsolidat.description: Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

https://schema.org/valueReference.name: valueReference
https://schema.org/valueReference.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

https://schema.org/activityFrequency.name: activityFrequency
https://schema.org/activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

https://schema.org/numberOfBedrooms.name: numberOfBedrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfBedrooms.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

https://schema.org/foundingDate.name: foundingDate
https://schema.org/foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

https://schema.org/recordingOf.name: recordingOf
https://schema.org/recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

https://schema.org/mapType.name: mapType
https://schema.org/mapType.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

https://schema.org/device.name: device
