https://schema.org/device.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

https://schema.org/relatedCondition.name: relatedCondition
https://schema.org/relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

https://schema.org/physicalRequirement.name: physicalRequirement
https://schema.org/physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

https://schema.org/renegotiableLoan.name: renegotiableLoan
https://schema.org/renegotiableLoan.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

https://schema.org/containedIn.name: containedIn
https://schema.org/containedIn.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

https://schema.org/authenticator.name: authenticator
https://schema.org/authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

https://schema.org/targetProduct.name: targetProduct
https://schema.org/targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

https://schema.org/bestRating.name: bestRating
https://schema.org/bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

https://schema.org/containsPlace.name: containsPlace
https://schema.org/containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

https://schema.org/bioChemInteraction.name: bioChemInteraction
https://schema.org/bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

https://schema.org/knowsLanguage.name: knowsLanguage
https://schema.org/knowsLanguage.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

https://schema.org/numberOfItems.name: numberOfItems
https://schema.org/numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

https://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVo.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
https://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVo.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

https://schema.org/rsvpResponse.name: rsvpResponse
https://schema.org/rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

https://schema.org/refundType.name: refundType
https://schema.org/refundType.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

https://schema.org/legislationIdentifier.name: legislationIdentifier
https://schema.org/legislationIdentifier.description: An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

https://schema.org/exerciseType.name: exerciseType
https://schema.org/exerciseType.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

https://schema.org/commentTime.name: commentTime
https://schema.org/commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

https://schema.org/addressLocality.name: addressLocality
https://schema.org/addressLocality.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

https://schema.org/productionDate.name: productionDate
https://schema.org/productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

https://schema.org/doseValue.name: doseValue
https://schema.org/doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

https://schema.org/applicationSubCategor.name: applicationSubCategory
https://schema.org/applicationSubCategor.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.name: spokenByCharacter
https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/contentRating.name: contentRating
https://schema.org/contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

https://schema.org/loanRepaymentForm.name: loanRepaymentForm
https://schema.org/loanRepaymentForm.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

https://schema.org/lodgingUnitDescriptio.name: lodgingUnitDescription
https://schema.org/lodgingUnitDescriptio.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

https://schema.org/inChI.name: inChI
https://schema.org/inChI.description: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

https://schema.org/bloodSupply.name: bloodSupply
https://schema.org/bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

https://schema.org/salaryUponCompletion.name: salaryUponCompletion
https://schema.org/salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

https://schema.org/fileSize.name: fileSize
https://schema.org/fileSize.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

https://schema.org/conditionsOfAccess.name: conditionsOfAccess
https://schema.org/conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

https://schema.org/discountCode.name: discountCode
https://schema.org/discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

https://schema.org/opponent.name: opponent
https://schema.org/opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

https://schema.org/fuelCapacity.name: fuelCapacity
https://schema.org/fuelCapacity.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

https://schema.org/location.name: location
https://schema.org/location.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

https://schema.org/paymentMethod.name: paymentMethod
https://schema.org/paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

https://schema.org/codeSampleType.name: codeSampleType
https://schema.org/codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

https://schema.org/itemOffered.name: itemOffered
https://schema.org/itemOffered.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

https://schema.org/scheduledPaymentDate.name: scheduledPaymentDate
https://schema.org/scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

https://schema.org/award.name: award
https://schema.org/award.description: An award won by or for this item.

https://schema.org/directApply.name: directApply
https://schema.org/directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

https://schema.org/billingStart.name: billingStart
https://schema.org/billingStart.description: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

https://schema.org/postalCodeEnd.name: postalCodeEnd
https://schema.org/postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

https://schema.org/variableMeasured.name: variableMeasured
https://schema.org/variableMeasured.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue.

https://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.name: healthPlanDrugTier
https://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.description: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

https://schema.org/dataset.name: dataset
https://schema.org/dataset.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

https://schema.org/departureBoatTerminal.name: departureBoatTerminal
https://schema.org/departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

https://schema.org/tourBookingPage.name: tourBookingPage
https://schema.org/tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

https://schema.org/constrainingProperty.name: constrainingProperty
https://schema.org/constrainingProperty.description:
Indicates a property used as a constraint to define a [[StatisticalPopulation]] with respect to the set of entities
  corresponding to an indicated type (via [[populationType]]).

https://schema.org/recipeInstructions.name: recipeInstructions
https://schema.org/recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

https://schema.org/error.name: error
https://schema.org/error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

https://schema.org/checkinTime.name: checkinTime
https://schema.org/checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

https://schema.org/availabilityStarts.name: availabilityStarts
https://schema.org/availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

https://schema.org/datePosted.name: datePosted
https://schema.org/datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

https://schema.org/supplyTo.name: supplyTo
https://schema.org/supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

https://schema.org/yearlyRevenue.name: yearlyRevenue
https://schema.org/yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

https://schema.org/performTime.name: performTime
https://schema.org/performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/toLocation.name: toLocation
https://schema.org/toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

https://schema.org/byMonthWeek.name: byMonthWeek
https://schema.org/byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

https://schema.org/member.name: member
https://schema.org/member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

https://schema.org/birthPlace.name: birthPlace
https://schema.org/birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

https://schema.org/chemicalRole.name: chemicalRole
https://schema.org/chemicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

https://schema.org/catalogNumber.name: catalogNumber
https://schema.org/catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

https://schema.org/nerveMotor.name: nerveMotor
https://schema.org/nerveMotor.description: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

https://schema.org/isAvailableGenericall.name: isAvailableGenerically
https://schema.org/isAvailableGenericall.description: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

https://schema.org/variesBy.name: variesBy
https://schema.org/variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

https://schema.org/ticketedSeat.name: ticketedSeat
https://schema.org/ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

https://schema.org/returnMethod.name: returnMethod

https://schema.org/value.name: value
https://schema.org/value.description:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/events.name: events
https://schema.org/events.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

https://schema.org/numberedPosition.name: numberedPosition
https://schema.org/numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

https://schema.org/actionAccessibilityRe.name: actionAccessibilityRequirement
https://schema.org/actionAccessibilityRe.description: A set of requirements that a must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specied, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

https://schema.org/billingDuration.name: billingDuration

https://schema.org/hasMenu.name: hasMenu

https://schema.org/accessModeSufficient.name: accessModeSufficient

https://schema.org/applicationContact.name: applicationContact

https://schema.org/availability.name: availability

https://schema.org/priceValidUntil.name: priceValidUntil

https://schema.org/releaseOf.name: releaseOf

https://schema.org/numberOfLoanPayments.name: numberOfLoanPayments

https://schema.org/foodEstablishment.name: foodEstablishment

https://schema.org/enginePower.name: enginePower
https://schema.org/enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

https://schema.org/publisherImprint.name: publisherImprint

https://schema.org/negativeNotes.name: negativeNotes

https://schema.org/firstAppearance.name: firstAppearance

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19MechVentPats.name: cvdNumC19MechVentPats

https://schema.org/temporalCoverage.name: temporalCoverage
https://schema.org/temporalCoverage.description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In
      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.
      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.
