https://schema.org/candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

https://schema.org/iswcCode.name: iswcCode
https://schema.org/iswcCode.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

https://schema.org/labelDetails.name: labelDetails
https://schema.org/labelDetails.description: Link to the drug's label details.

https://schema.org/exerciseCourse.name: exerciseCourse
https://schema.org/exerciseCourse.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

https://schema.org/proteinContent.name: proteinContent
https://schema.org/proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

https://schema.org/documentation.name: documentation
https://schema.org/documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

https://schema.org/deliveryMethod.name: deliveryMethod
https://schema.org/deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

https://schema.org/question.name: question
https://schema.org/question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

https://schema.org/estimatedSalary.name: estimatedSalary
https://schema.org/estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

https://schema.org/roofLoad.name: roofLoad
https://schema.org/roofLoad.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/cvdFacilityCounty.name: cvdFacilityCounty
https://schema.org/cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

https://schema.org/ratingCount.name: ratingCount
https://schema.org/ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

https://schema.org/encodings.name: encodings
https://schema.org/encodings.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/hasBioPolymerSequence.name: hasBioPolymerSequence
https://schema.org/hasBioPolymerSequence.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEnity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

https://schema.org/driveWheelConfigurati.name: driveWheelConfiguration
https://schema.org/driveWheelConfigurati.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

https://schema.org/track.name: track
https://schema.org/track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

https://schema.org/risks.name: risks
https://schema.org/risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

https://schema.org/hasEnergyConsumptionD.name: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
https://schema.org/hasEnergyConsumptionD.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

https://schema.org/sportsTeam.name: sportsTeam
https://schema.org/sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

https://schema.org/intensity.name: intensity
https://schema.org/intensity.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

https://schema.org/employmentUnit.name: employmentUnit
https://schema.org/employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

https://schema.org/leaseLength.name: leaseLength
https://schema.org/leaseLength.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

https://schema.org/trailer.name: trailer
https://schema.org/trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

https://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.name: includedInDataCatalog
https://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

https://schema.org/requiresSubscription.name: requiresSubscription
https://schema.org/requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

https://schema.org/administrationRoute.name: administrationRoute
https://schema.org/administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

https://schema.org/ownershipFundingInfo.name: ownershipFundingInfo
https://schema.org/ownershipFundingInfo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

https://schema.org/hasMolecularFunction.name: hasMolecularFunction
https://schema.org/hasMolecularFunction.description: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

https://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.name: accessibilityHazard
https://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 ([WebSchemas wiki lists possible values](http://www.w3.org/wiki/WebSchemas/Accessibility)).

https://schema.org/albumProductionType.name: albumProductionType
https://schema.org/albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

https://schema.org/drugUnit.name: drugUnit
https://schema.org/drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

https://schema.org/subjectOf.name: subjectOf
https://schema.org/subjectOf.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

https://schema.org/propertyID.name: propertyID
https://schema.org/propertyID.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

https://schema.org/cholesterolContent.name: cholesterolContent
https://schema.org/cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

https://schema.org/accountablePerson.name: accountablePerson
https://schema.org/accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/archiveHeld.name: archiveHeld
https://schema.org/archiveHeld.description: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

https://schema.org/recordedIn.name: recordedIn
https://schema.org/recordedIn.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

https://schema.org/encodesBioChemEntity.name: encodesBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

https://schema.org/maximumEnrollment.name: maximumEnrollment
https://schema.org/maximumEnrollment.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

https://schema.org/itinerary.name: itinerary
https://schema.org/itinerary.description: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

https://schema.org/sampleType.name: sampleType
https://schema.org/sampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

https://schema.org/jobStartDate.name: jobStartDate
https://schema.org/jobStartDate.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

https://schema.org/interactivityType.name: interactivityType
https://schema.org/interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

https://schema.org/partOfTrip.name: partOfTrip
https://schema.org/partOfTrip.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

https://schema.org/maxValue.name: maxValue
https://schema.org/maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

https://schema.org/branchCode.name: branchCode
https://schema.org/branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

https://schema.org/expertConsiderations.name: expertConsiderations
https://schema.org/expertConsiderations.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

https://schema.org/representativeOfPage.name: representativeOfPage
https://schema.org/representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

https://schema.org/priceRange.name: priceRange
https://schema.org/priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

https://schema.org/utterances.name: utterances
https://schema.org/utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

https://schema.org/interactionStatistic.name: interactionStatistic
https://schema.org/interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

https://schema.org/trainingSalary.name: trainingSalary
https://schema.org/trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

https://schema.org/resultComment.name: resultComment
https://schema.org/resultComment.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

https://schema.org/accessibilityControl.name: accessibilityControl
https://schema.org/accessibilityControl.description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource ([WebSchemas wiki lists possible values](http://www.w3.org/wiki/WebSchemas/Accessibility)).

https://schema.org/study.name: study
https://schema.org/study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

https://schema.org/hasCredential.name: hasCredential
https://schema.org/hasCredential.description: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

https://schema.org/ratingValue.name: ratingValue
https://schema.org/ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/awayTeam.name: awayTeam
https://schema.org/awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

https://schema.org/episodeNumber.name: episodeNumber
https://schema.org/episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

https://schema.org/additionalProperty.name: additionalProperty
https://schema.org/additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

https://schema.org/creativeWorkStatus.name: creativeWorkStatus
https://schema.org/creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

https://schema.org/loanTerm.name: loanTerm
https://schema.org/loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

https://schema.org/sportsActivityLocatio.name: sportsActivityLocation
https://schema.org/sportsActivityLocatio.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

https://schema.org/comprisedOf.name: comprisedOf
https://schema.org/comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

https://schema.org/availableService.name: availableService
https://schema.org/availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

https://schema.org/inverseOf.name: inverseOf
https://schema.org/inverseOf.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

https://schema.org/category.name: category
https://schema.org/category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

https://schema.org/vatID.name: vatID
https://schema.org/vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

https://schema.org/appearance.name: appearance
https://schema.org/appearance.description: Indicates an occurence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/postalCodePrefix.name: postalCodePrefix
https://schema.org/postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

https://schema.org/orderItemNumber.name: orderItemNumber
https://schema.org/orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

https://schema.org/busName.name: busName
https://schema.org/busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

https://schema.org/transmissionMethod.name: transmissionMethod
https://schema.org/transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

https://schema.org/frequency.name: frequency
https://schema.org/frequency.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

https://schema.org/termCode.name: termCode
https://schema.org/termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]]

https://schema.org/interactionCount.name: interactionCount
https://schema.org/interactionCount.description: This property is deprecated, alongside the UserInteraction types on which it depended.

https://schema.org/arrivalGate.name: arrivalGate
https://schema.org/arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

https://schema.org/reviewAspect.name: reviewAspect
https://schema.org/reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

https://schema.org/downPayment.name: downPayment
https://schema.org/downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

https://schema.org/orderStatus.name: orderStatus
https://schema.org/orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

https://schema.org/realEstateAgent.name: realEstateAgent
https://schema.org/realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

https://schema.org/geoContains.name: geoContains
https://schema.org/geoContains.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/reviewCount.name: reviewCount
https://schema.org/reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

https://schema.org/gtin12.name: gtin12
https://schema.org/gtin12.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/actionPlatform.name: actionPlatform
https://schema.org/actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

https://schema.org/postalCodeRange.name: postalCodeRange
https://schema.org/postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

https://schema.org/catalog.name: catalog
https://schema.org/catalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

https://schema.org/requiredGender.name: requiredGender
https://schema.org/requiredGender.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

https://schema.org/course.name: course
https://schema.org/course.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

https://schema.org/printPage.name: printPage
https://schema.org/printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

https://schema.org/familyName.name: familyName
https://schema.org/familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

https://schema.org/clincalPharmacology.name: clincalPharmacology
https://schema.org/clincalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

https://schema.org/equal.name: equal
https://schema.org/equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

https://schema.org/thumbnailUrl.name: thumbnailUrl
https://schema.org/thumbnailUrl.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

https://schema.org/gameLocation.name: gameLocation
https://schema.org/gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

https://schema.org/associatedMedia.name: associatedMedia
https://schema.org/associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

https://schema.org/contentUrl.name: contentUrl
https://schema.org/contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

https://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.name: incentiveCompensation
https://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

https://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.name: isBasedOnUrl
https://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

https://schema.org/embeddedTextCaption.name: embeddedTextCaption
https://schema.org/embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

https://schema.org/diagram.name: diagram
https://schema.org/diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

https://schema.org/founders.name: founders
https://schema.org/founders.description: A person who founded this organization.

https://schema.org/lesser.name: lesser
https://schema.org/lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

https://schema.org/hasMeasurement.name: hasMeasurement
https://schema.org/hasMeasurement.description: A product measurement, for example the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, or the gauge of a screw. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

https://schema.org/webCheckinTime.name: webCheckinTime
https://schema.org/webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

https://schema.org/releaseDate.name: releaseDate
https://schema.org/releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

https://schema.org/dosageForm.name: dosageForm
https://schema.org/dosageForm.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

https://schema.org/sugarContent.name: sugarContent
https://schema.org/sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

https://schema.org/suitableForDiet.name: suitableForDiet
https://schema.org/suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

https://schema.org/byMonth.name: byMonth
https://schema.org/byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

https://schema.org/reservationFor.name: reservationFor
https://schema.org/reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

https://schema.org/diet.name: diet
https://schema.org/diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

https://schema.org/rxcui.name: rxcui
https://schema.org/rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

https://schema.org/blogPosts.name: blogPosts
https://schema.org/blogPosts.description: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

https://schema.org/accommodationCategory.name: accommodationCategory
https://schema.org/accommodationCategory.description: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields  for suggested values).

https://schema.org/totalPrice.name: totalPrice
https://schema.org/totalPrice.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/downloadUrl.name: downloadUrl
https://schema.org/downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

https://schema.org/previousItem.name: previousItem
https://schema.org/previousItem.description: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

https://schema.org/inAlbum.name: inAlbum
https://schema.org/inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

https://schema.org/predecessorOf.name: predecessorOf
https://schema.org/predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

https://schema.org/numberOfEmployees.name: numberOfEmployees
https://schema.org/numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

https://schema.org/geoCoveredBy.name: geoCoveredBy
https://schema.org/geoCoveredBy.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/actors.name: actors
https://schema.org/actors.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.name: benefitsSummaryUrl
https://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

https://schema.org/pagination.name: pagination
https://schema.org/pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

https://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.name: acceptedPaymentMethod
https://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

https://schema.org/xpath.name: xpath
https://schema.org/xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

https://schema.org/workTranslation.name: workTranslation
https://schema.org/workTranslation.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. 西遊記 has an English workTranslation “Journey to the West”,a German workTranslation “Monkeys Pilgerfahrt” and a Vietnamese  translation Tây du ký bình khảo.

https://schema.org/minimumPaymentDue.name: minimumPaymentDue
https://schema.org/minimumPaymentDue.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

https://schema.org/potentialAction.name: potentialAction
https://schema.org/potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

https://schema.org/domiciledMortgage.name: domiciledMortgage
https://schema.org/domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

https://schema.org/hasMerchantReturnPoli.name: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
https://schema.org/hasMerchantReturnPoli.description: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

https://schema.org/associatedArticle.name: associatedArticle
https://schema.org/associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

https://schema.org/courseWorkload.name: courseWorkload
https://schema.org/courseWorkload.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

https://schema.org/containedInPlace.name: containedInPlace
https://schema.org/containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

https://schema.org/distribution.name: distribution
https://schema.org/distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

https://schema.org/menu.name: menu
https://schema.org/menu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

https://schema.org/productID.name: productID
https://schema.org/productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

https://schema.org/permittedUsage.name: permittedUsage
https://schema.org/permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

https://schema.org/partOfSeason.name: partOfSeason
https://schema.org/partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorType.name: vehicleInteriorType
https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

https://schema.org/sdPublisher.name: sdPublisher
https://schema.org/sdPublisher.description:
Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The
[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

https://schema.org/maxPrice.name: maxPrice
https://schema.org/maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

https://schema.org/cvdNumVent.name: cvdNumVent
https://schema.org/cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

https://schema.org/floorLimit.name: floorLimit
https://schema.org/floorLimit.description: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

https://schema.org/follows.name: follows
https://schema.org/follows.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

https://schema.org/line.name: line
https://schema.org/line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

https://schema.org/affiliation.name: affiliation
https://schema.org/affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

https://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.name: evidenceOrigin
https://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

https://schema.org/producer.name: producer
https://schema.org/producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

https://schema.org/publisher.name: publisher
https://schema.org/publisher.description: The publisher of the creative work.

https://schema.org/multipleValues.name: multipleValues
https://schema.org/multipleValues.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

https://schema.org/newsUpdatesAndGuideli.name: newsUpdatesAndGuidelines
https://schema.org/newsUpdatesAndGuideli.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

https://schema.org/superEvent.name: superEvent
https://schema.org/superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

https://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.name: accessibilitySummary
https://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

https://schema.org/numChildren.name: numChildren
https://schema.org/numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

https://schema.org/transitTime.name: transitTime
https://schema.org/transitTime.description: The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

https://schema.org/numberOfPreviousOwner.name: numberOfPreviousOwners
https://schema.org/numberOfPreviousOwner.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

https://schema.org/taxonRank.name: taxonRank
https://schema.org/taxonRank.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary – (typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs).

https://schema.org/legislationChanges.name: legislationChanges
https://schema.org/legislationChanges.description: Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the legislationConsolidates property.

https://schema.org/jobLocation.name: jobLocation
https://schema.org/jobLocation.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

https://schema.org/totalJobOpenings.name: totalJobOpenings
https://schema.org/totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

https://schema.org/workHours.name: workHours
https://schema.org/workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

https://schema.org/payload.name: payload
https://schema.org/payload.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/publishingPrinciples.name: publishingPrinciples
https://schema.org/publishingPrinciples.description:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

https://schema.org/numAdults.name: numAdults
https://schema.org/numAdults.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

https://schema.org/partOfSeries.name: partOfSeries
https://schema.org/partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

https://schema.org/legislationResponsibl.name: legislationResponsible
https://schema.org/legislationResponsibl.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

https://schema.org/serviceOperator.name: serviceOperator
https://schema.org/serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

https://schema.org/offersPrescriptionByM.name: offersPrescriptionByMail
https://schema.org/offersPrescriptionByM.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

https://schema.org/seasons.name: seasons
https://schema.org/seasons.description: A season in a media series.

https://schema.org/valuePattern.name: valuePattern
https://schema.org/valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

https://schema.org/accessMode.name: accessMode
https://schema.org/accessMode.description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

https://schema.org/additionalType.name: additionalType
https://schema.org/additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

https://schema.org/typicalAgeRange.name: typicalAgeRange
https://schema.org/typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

https://schema.org/result.name: result
https://schema.org/result.description: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote *a book*.

https://schema.org/bed.name: bed
https://schema.org/bed.description:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

https://schema.org/claimReviewed.name: claimReviewed
https://schema.org/claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

https://schema.org/wordCount.name: wordCount
https://schema.org/wordCount.description: The number of words in the text of the Article.

https://schema.org/numberOfBathroomsTota.name: numberOfBathroomsTotal
https://schema.org/numberOfBathroomsTota.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

https://schema.org/interestRate.name: interestRate
https://schema.org/interestRate.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

https://schema.org/contentType.name: contentType
https://schema.org/contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

https://schema.org/penciler.name: penciler
https://schema.org/penciler.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

https://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode.name: eventAttendanceMode
https://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode.description: The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

https://schema.org/priceComponent.name: priceComponent
https://schema.org/priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

https://schema.org/legislationLegalForce.name: legislationLegalForce
https://schema.org/legislationLegalForce.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

https://schema.org/itemListOrder.name: itemListOrder
https://schema.org/itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

https://schema.org/jobTitle.name: jobTitle
https://schema.org/jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

https://schema.org/parentItem.name: parentItem
https://schema.org/parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

https://schema.org/lowPrice.name: lowPrice
https://schema.org/lowPrice.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/teaches.name: teaches
https://schema.org/teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

https://schema.org/namedPosition.name: namedPosition
https://schema.org/namedPosition.description: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

https://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.name: broadcastAffiliateOf
https://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

https://schema.org/latitude.name: latitude
https://schema.org/latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

https://schema.org/tickerSymbol.name: tickerSymbol
https://schema.org/tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

https://schema.org/subTest.name: subTest
https://schema.org/subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

https://schema.org/seatSection.name: seatSection
https://schema.org/seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

https://schema.org/molecularFormula.name: molecularFormula
https://schema.org/molecularFormula.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

https://schema.org/assembly.name: assembly
https://schema.org/assembly.description: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

https://schema.org/merchantReturnLink.name: merchantReturnLink
https://schema.org/merchantReturnLink.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

https://schema.org/recordLabel.name: recordLabel
https://schema.org/recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

https://schema.org/brand.name: brand
https://schema.org/brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

https://schema.org/membershipPointsEarne.name: membershipPointsEarned
https://schema.org/membershipPointsEarne.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (e.g. stars, miles, etc.)

https://schema.org/associatedClaimReview.name: associatedClaimReview
https://schema.org/associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

https://schema.org/guideline.name: guideline
https://schema.org/guideline.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

https://schema.org/version.name: version
https://schema.org/version.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

https://schema.org/givenName.name: givenName
https://schema.org/givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

https://schema.org/carbohydrateContent.name: carbohydrateContent
https://schema.org/carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

https://schema.org/dateModified.name: dateModified
https://schema.org/dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

https://schema.org/timeRequired.name: timeRequired
https://schema.org/timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'PT30M', 'PT1H25M'.

https://schema.org/naturalProgression.name: naturalProgression
https://schema.org/naturalProgression.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

https://schema.org/endorsers.name: endorsers
https://schema.org/endorsers.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HospPats.name: cvdNumC19HospPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

https://schema.org/code.name: code
https://schema.org/code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

https://schema.org/reservedTicket.name: reservedTicket
https://schema.org/reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.description: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

https://schema.org/drainsTo.name: drainsTo
https://schema.org/drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

https://schema.org/sdDatePublished.name: sdDatePublished
https://schema.org/sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]]

https://schema.org/citation.name: citation
https://schema.org/citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

https://schema.org/offeredBy.name: offeredBy
https://schema.org/offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

https://schema.org/pickupTime.name: pickupTime
https://schema.org/pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

https://schema.org/endDate.name: endDate
https://schema.org/endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

https://schema.org/loanPaymentFrequency.name: loanPaymentFrequency
https://schema.org/loanPaymentFrequency.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

https://schema.org/bodyType.name: bodyType
https://schema.org/bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

https://schema.org/engineDisplacement.name: engineDisplacement
https://schema.org/engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/dateCreated.name: dateCreated
https://schema.org/dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

https://schema.org/playMode.name: playMode
https://schema.org/playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

https://schema.org/shippingDestination.name: shippingDestination
https://schema.org/shippingDestination.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.

https://schema.org/readBy.name: readBy
https://schema.org/readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

https://schema.org/governmentBenefitsInf.name: governmentBenefitsInfo
https://schema.org/governmentBenefitsInf.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

https://schema.org/geoEquals.name: geoEquals
https://schema.org/geoEquals.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

https://schema.org/suggestedAnswer.name: suggestedAnswer
https://schema.org/suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

https://schema.org/screenCount.name: screenCount
https://schema.org/screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

https://schema.org/contributor.name: contributor
https://schema.org/contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

https://schema.org/taxID.name: taxID
https://schema.org/taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

https://schema.org/publicationType.name: publicationType
https://schema.org/publicationType.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

https://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMeth.name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMeth.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

https://schema.org/hasPOS.name: hasPOS
https://schema.org/hasPOS.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

https://schema.org/originalMediaLink.name: originalMediaLink
https://schema.org/originalMediaLink.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

https://schema.org/returnLabelSource.name: returnLabelSource
https://schema.org/returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

https://schema.org/incentives.name: incentives
https://schema.org/incentives.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

https://schema.org/collection.name: collection
https://schema.org/collection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

https://schema.org/runsTo.name: runsTo
https://schema.org/runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

https://schema.org/eventStatus.name: eventStatus
https://schema.org/eventStatus.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HOPats.name: cvdNumC19HOPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

https://schema.org/subEvent.name: subEvent
https://schema.org/subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

https://schema.org/hasDriveThroughServic.name: hasDriveThroughService
https://schema.org/hasDriveThroughServic.description: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

https://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.name: exerciseRelatedDiet
https://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

https://schema.org/actionApplication.name: actionApplication
https://schema.org/actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

https://schema.org/highPrice.name: highPrice
https://schema.org/highPrice.description:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/runtime.name: runtime
https://schema.org/runtime.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0).

https://schema.org/longitude.name: longitude
https://schema.org/longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

https://schema.org/acquireLicensePage.name: acquireLicensePage
https://schema.org/acquireLicensePage.description: Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

https://schema.org/inSupportOf.name: inSupportOf
https://schema.org/inSupportOf.description: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

https://schema.org/landlord.name: landlord
https://schema.org/landlord.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

https://schema.org/fromLocation.name: fromLocation
https://schema.org/fromLocation.description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

https://schema.org/taxonomicRange.name: taxonomicRange
https://schema.org/taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in someway related to the BioChemEntity.

https://schema.org/bankAccountType.name: bankAccountType
https://schema.org/bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.name: globalLocationNumber
https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.description: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

https://schema.org/durationOfWarranty.name: durationOfWarranty
https://schema.org/durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

https://schema.org/mentions.name: mentions
https://schema.org/mentions.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

https://schema.org/featureList.name: featureList
https://schema.org/featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

https://schema.org/audienceType.name: audienceType
https://schema.org/audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

https://schema.org/translationOfWork.name: translationOfWork
https://schema.org/translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. 物种起源 is a translationOf “On the Origin of Species”

https://schema.org/clipNumber.name: clipNumber
https://schema.org/clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

https://schema.org/permissionType.name: permissionType
https://schema.org/permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

https://schema.org/image.name: image
https://schema.org/image.description: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

https://schema.org/carrierRequirements.name: carrierRequirements
https://schema.org/carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

https://schema.org/weightTotal.name: weightTotal
https://schema.org/weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/department.name: department
https://schema.org/department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

https://schema.org/availableChannel.name: availableChannel
https://schema.org/availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.name: customerRemorseReturnFees
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

https://schema.org/encodingType.name: encodingType
https://schema.org/encodingType.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

https://schema.org/bookingTime.name: bookingTime
https://schema.org/bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

https://schema.org/query.name: query
https://schema.org/query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

https://schema.org/checkoutTime.name: checkoutTime
https://schema.org/checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

https://schema.org/publicAccess.name: publicAccess
https://schema.org/publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value

https://schema.org/repetitions.name: repetitions
https://schema.org/repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage.name: mainContentOfPage
https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

https://schema.org/vehicleModelDate.name: vehicleModelDate
https://schema.org/vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

https://schema.org/accelerationTime.name: accelerationTime
https://schema.org/accelerationTime.description:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

https://schema.org/subtitleLanguage.name: subtitleLanguage
https://schema.org/subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

https://schema.org/meetsEmissionStandard.name: meetsEmissionStandard
https://schema.org/meetsEmissionStandard.description: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

https://schema.org/creditedTo.name: creditedTo

https://schema.org/validThrough.name: validThrough
https://schema.org/validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

https://schema.org/vehicleSpecialUsage.name: vehicleSpecialUsage
https://schema.org/vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

https://schema.org/addressRegion.name: addressRegion
https://schema.org/addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country)

https://schema.org/paymentAccepted.name: paymentAccepted
https://schema.org/paymentAccepted.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

https://schema.org/jobImmediateStart.name: jobImmediateStart
https://schema.org/jobImmediateStart.description: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

https://schema.org/actionOption.name: actionOption
https://schema.org/actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

https://schema.org/broadcastSignalModula.name: broadcastSignalModulation
https://schema.org/broadcastSignalModula.description: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

https://schema.org/numberOfBeds.name: numberOfBeds
https://schema.org/numberOfBeds.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

https://schema.org/differentialDiagnosis.name: differentialDiagnosis
https://schema.org/differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

https://schema.org/providerMobility.name: providerMobility
https://schema.org/providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

https://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.name: infectiousAgentClass
https://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.description: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

https://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.name: expectsAcceptanceOf
https://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

https://schema.org/deliveryLeadTime.name: deliveryLeadTime
https://schema.org/deliveryLeadTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

https://schema.org/smiles.name: smiles
https://schema.org/smiles.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

https://schema.org/seatRow.name: seatRow
https://schema.org/seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

https://schema.org/musicArrangement.name: musicArrangement
https://schema.org/musicArrangement.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

https://schema.org/accessCode.name: accessCode
https://schema.org/accessCode.description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

https://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.name: estimatesRiskOf
https://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

https://schema.org/publishedBy.name: publishedBy
https://schema.org/publishedBy.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

https://schema.org/sender.name: sender
https://schema.org/sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

https://schema.org/scheduleTimezone.name: scheduleTimezone
https://schema.org/scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

https://schema.org/molecularWeight.name: molecularWeight
https://schema.org/molecularWeight.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

https://schema.org/letterer.description: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

https://schema.org/tributary.name: tributary
https://schema.org/tributary.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

https://schema.org/primaryImageOfPage.name: primaryImageOfPage
https://schema.org/primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

https://schema.org/geoOverlaps.name: geoOverlaps

https://schema.org/totalTime.name: totalTime

https://schema.org/screenshot.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

https://schema.org/chemicalComposition.name: chemicalComposition

https://schema.org/messageAttachment.name: messageAttachment
https://schema.org/messageAttachment.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

https://schema.org/assesses.name: assesses

https://schema.org/honorificSuffix.description: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.

https://schema.org/pregnancyWarning.name: pregnancyWarning
https://schema.org/pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

https://schema.org/paymentStatus.name: paymentStatus
https://schema.org/paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

https://schema.org/homeTeam.name: homeTeam
https://schema.org/homeTeam.description: The home team in a sports event.

https://schema.org/typeOfGood.name: typeOfGood

https://schema.org/medicineSystem.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

https://schema.org/byMonthDay.name: byMonthDay
https://schema.org/byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

https://schema.org/securityScreening.name: securityScreening
https://schema.org/securityScreening.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

https://schema.org/domainIncludes.name: domainIncludes
https://schema.org/domainIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

https://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.name: hasBroadcastChannel
https://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.description: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

https://schema.org/ingredients.name: ingredients
https://schema.org/ingredients.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

https://schema.org/starRating.name: starRating
https://schema.org/starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

https://schema.org/discountCurrency.name: discountCurrency
https://schema.org/discountCurrency.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/recipeYield.name: recipeYield
https://schema.org/recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

https://schema.org/ratingExplanation.name: ratingExplanation
https://schema.org/ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

https://schema.org/cookingMethod.name: cookingMethod
https://schema.org/cookingMethod.description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

https://schema.org/sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

https://schema.org/employerOverview.name: employerOverview
https://schema.org/employerOverview.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

https://schema.org/serviceUrl.name: serviceUrl
https://schema.org/serviceUrl.description: The website to access the service.

https://schema.org/mealService.name: mealService
https://schema.org/mealService.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

https://schema.org/identifyingExam.name: identifyingExam
https://schema.org/identifyingExam.description: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

https://schema.org/numberOfAvailableAcco.name: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
https://schema.org/numberOfAvailableAcco.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

https://schema.org/programPrerequisites.name: programPrerequisites
https://schema.org/programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

https://schema.org/numberOfSeasons.name: numberOfSeasons
https://schema.org/numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

https://schema.org/event.name: event
https://schema.org/event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

https://schema.org/recourseLoan.name: recourseLoan
https://schema.org/recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

https://schema.org/speakable.name: speakable
https://schema.org/speakable.description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

https://schema.org/playersOnline.name: playersOnline
https://schema.org/playersOnline.description: Number of players on the server.

https://schema.org/workFeatured.name: workFeatured
https://schema.org/workFeatured.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

https://schema.org/legalName.name: legalName
https://schema.org/legalName.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

https://schema.org/relevantSpecialty.name: relevantSpecialty
https://schema.org/relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBedsOcc.name: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

https://schema.org/inProductGroupWithID.name: inProductGroupWithID
https://schema.org/inProductGroupWithID.description: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

https://schema.org/geo.name: geo
https://schema.org/geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

https://schema.org/providesService.name: providesService
https://schema.org/providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

https://schema.org/structuralClass.name: structuralClass
https://schema.org/structuralClass.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

https://schema.org/containsSeason.name: containsSeason
https://schema.org/containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

https://schema.org/deliveryTime.name: deliveryTime
https://schema.org/deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

https://schema.org/subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

https://schema.org/affectedBy.name: affectedBy
https://schema.org/affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

https://schema.org/director.description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/returnPolicyCategory.name: returnPolicyCategory
https://schema.org/returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

https://schema.org/tongueWeight.name: tongueWeight
https://schema.org/tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR)

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/hasEnergyEfficiencyCa.name: hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
https://schema.org/hasEnergyEfficiencyCa.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

https://schema.org/surface.name: surface

https://schema.org/saturatedFatContent.name: saturatedFatContent
https://schema.org/saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

https://schema.org/fatContent.name: fatContent
https://schema.org/fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

https://schema.org/amenityFeature.name: amenityFeature
https://schema.org/amenityFeature.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.
