https://schema.org/playerType.name: playerType
https://schema.org/playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

https://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPer.name: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
https://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPer.description: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

https://schema.org/softwareRequirements.name: softwareRequirements
https://schema.org/softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

https://schema.org/guidelineSubject.name: guidelineSubject
https://schema.org/guidelineSubject.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

https://schema.org/dateline.name: dateline
https://schema.org/dateline.description:
A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]].

Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

https://schema.org/billingIncrement.name: billingIncrement
https://schema.org/billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

https://schema.org/paymentDue.name: paymentDue
https://schema.org/paymentDue.description: The date that payment is due.

https://schema.org/userInteractionCount.name: userInteractionCount
https://schema.org/userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

https://schema.org/subOrganization.name: subOrganization
https://schema.org/subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

https://schema.org/warranty.name: warranty
https://schema.org/warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

https://schema.org/eligibleDuration.name: eligibleDuration
https://schema.org/eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

https://schema.org/numberOfPartialBathro.name: numberOfPartialBathrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfPartialBathro.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

https://schema.org/requiredMinAge.name: requiredMinAge
https://schema.org/requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

https://schema.org/orderItemStatus.name: orderItemStatus
https://schema.org/orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

https://schema.org/modelDate.name: modelDate

https://schema.org/abstract.name: abstract
https://schema.org/abstract.description: An abstract is a short description that summarizes a [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/greater.name: greater

https://schema.org/replyToUrl.name: replyToUrl

https://schema.org/carrier.name: carrier
https://schema.org/carrier.description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

https://schema.org/answerCount.name: answerCount
https://schema.org/answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

https://schema.org/strengthUnit.name: strengthUnit
https://schema.org/strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

https://schema.org/serviceSmsNumber.name: serviceSmsNumber
https://schema.org/serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

https://schema.org/educationalUse.name: educationalUse

https://schema.org/box.name: box
https://schema.org/box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

https://schema.org/signOrSymptom.name: signOrSymptom

https://schema.org/serviceOutput.name: serviceOutput
https://schema.org/serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

https://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.name: beneficiaryBank
https://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

https://schema.org/itemListElement.name: itemListElement
https://schema.org/itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

https://schema.org/duplicateTherapy.name: duplicateTherapy
https://schema.org/duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

https://schema.org/exceptDate.name: exceptDate
https://schema.org/exceptDate.description:
Defines a [[Date]] or [[DateTime]] during which a scheduled [[Event]] will not take place. The property allows exceptions to
      a [[Schedule]] to be specified. If an exception is specified as a [[DateTime]] then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time
      should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a [[Date]] then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be
      excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.

https://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.name: hasCategoryCode
https://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.description: A Category code contained in this code set.

https://schema.org/recommendationStrengt.name: recommendationStrength

https://schema.org/rangeIncludes.name: rangeIncludes

https://schema.org/skills.name: skills

https://schema.org/petsAllowed.name: petsAllowed
https://schema.org/petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

https://schema.org/diagnosis.name: diagnosis

https://schema.org/owns.name: owns

https://schema.org/maximumIntake.name: maximumIntake
https://schema.org/maximumIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

https://schema.org/isGift.name: isGift

https://schema.org/thumbnail.name: thumbnail
