https://schema.org/instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

https://schema.org/floorLevel.name: floorLevel
https://schema.org/floorLevel.description:
The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting
  systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

https://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.name: annualPercentageRate
https://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

https://schema.org/productSupported.name: productSupported
https://schema.org/productSupported.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

https://schema.org/providesBroadcastServ.name: providesBroadcastService
https://schema.org/providesBroadcastServ.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

https://schema.org/supersededBy.name: supersededBy
https://schema.org/supersededBy.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

https://schema.org/applicantLocationRequ.name: applicantLocationRequirements
https://schema.org/applicantLocationRequ.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

https://schema.org/codeRepository.name: codeRepository
https://schema.org/codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex).

https://schema.org/gtin8.name: gtin8
https://schema.org/gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/material.name: material
https://schema.org/material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

https://schema.org/additionalVariable.name: additionalVariable
https://schema.org/additionalVariable.description: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

https://schema.org/partOfEpisode.name: partOfEpisode
https://schema.org/partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

https://schema.org/inStoreReturnsOffered.name: inStoreReturnsOffered
https://schema.org/inStoreReturnsOffered.description: Are in-store returns offered? (for more advanced return methods use the [[returnMethod]] property)

https://schema.org/doseSchedule.name: doseSchedule
https://schema.org/doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

https://schema.org/beforeMedia.name: beforeMedia
https://schema.org/beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

https://schema.org/character.name: character
https://schema.org/character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

https://schema.org/contactlessPayment.name: contactlessPayment
https://schema.org/contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

https://schema.org/maximumPhysicalAttend.name: maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumPhysicalAttend.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

https://schema.org/seeks.name: seeks
https://schema.org/seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

https://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.name: biomechnicalClass
https://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

https://schema.org/inventoryLevel.name: inventoryLevel
https://schema.org/inventoryLevel.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

https://schema.org/articleSection.name: articleSection
https://schema.org/articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

https://schema.org/programMembershipUsed.name: programMembershipUsed
https://schema.org/programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

https://schema.org/timeToComplete.name: timeToComplete
https://schema.org/timeToComplete.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

https://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.name: expectedPrognosis
https://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.description: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

https://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.name: exchangeRateSpread
https://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

https://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.name: isLiveBroadcast
https://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

https://schema.org/mileageFromOdometer.name: mileageFromOdometer
https://schema.org/mileageFromOdometer.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

https://schema.org/doseUnit.name: doseUnit
https://schema.org/doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

https://schema.org/gtin.name: gtin
https://schema.org/gtin.description: A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties. The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) express GTINs as URLs. A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged.

https://schema.org/legislationLegalValue.name: legislationLegalValue
https://schema.org/legislationLegalValue.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

https://schema.org/endorsee.name: endorsee
https://schema.org/endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

https://schema.org/cvdFacilityId.name: cvdFacilityId
https://schema.org/cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

https://schema.org/stepValue.name: stepValue
https://schema.org/stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

https://schema.org/benefits.name: benefits
https://schema.org/benefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

https://schema.org/slogan.name: slogan
https://schema.org/slogan.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

https://schema.org/productionCompany.name: productionCompany
https://schema.org/productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

https://schema.org/copyrightNotice.name: copyrightNotice
https://schema.org/copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

https://schema.org/object.name: object
https://schema.org/object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read *a book*.

https://schema.org/participant.name: participant
https://schema.org/participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

https://schema.org/paymentMethodId.name: paymentMethodId
https://schema.org/paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

https://schema.org/musicReleaseFormat.name: musicReleaseFormat
https://schema.org/musicReleaseFormat.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

https://schema.org/memberOf.name: memberOf
https://schema.org/memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

https://schema.org/tracks.name: tracks
https://schema.org/tracks.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

https://schema.org/mathExpression.name: mathExpression
https://schema.org/mathExpression.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

https://schema.org/mediaItemAppearance.name: mediaItemAppearance
https://schema.org/mediaItemAppearance.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

https://schema.org/vehicleIdentification.name: vehicleIdentificationNumber
https://schema.org/vehicleIdentification.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

https://schema.org/tissueSample.name: tissueSample
https://schema.org/tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

https://schema.org/primaryPrevention.name: primaryPrevention
https://schema.org/primaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

https://schema.org/closes.name: closes
https://schema.org/closes.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

https://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.name: broadcastOfEvent
https://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

https://schema.org/quest.name: quest
https://schema.org/quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

https://schema.org/hasPart.name: hasPart
https://schema.org/hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

https://schema.org/speed.name: speed
https://schema.org/speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]] should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

https://schema.org/subReservation.name: subReservation
https://schema.org/subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

https://schema.org/leiCode.name: leiCode
https://schema.org/leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

https://schema.org/customer.name: customer
https://schema.org/customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

https://schema.org/artist.name: artist
https://schema.org/artist.description:
The primary artist for a work
    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

https://schema.org/dataFeedElement.name: dataFeedElement
https://schema.org/dataFeedElement.description: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

https://schema.org/quarantineGuidelines.name: quarantineGuidelines
https://schema.org/quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/valueMinLength.name: valueMinLength
https://schema.org/valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

https://schema.org/dateVehicleFirstRegis.name: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
https://schema.org/dateVehicleFirstRegis.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

https://schema.org/legislationJurisdicti.name: legislationJurisdiction
https://schema.org/legislationJurisdicti.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

https://schema.org/specialty.name: specialty
https://schema.org/specialty.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

https://schema.org/includesObject.name: includesObject
https://schema.org/includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

https://schema.org/lodgingUnitType.name: lodgingUnitType
https://schema.org/lodgingUnitType.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

https://schema.org/cvdCollectionDate.name: cvdCollectionDate
https://schema.org/cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

https://schema.org/dissolutionDate.name: dissolutionDate
https://schema.org/dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

https://schema.org/proficiencyLevel.name: proficiencyLevel
https://schema.org/proficiencyLevel.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

https://schema.org/deliveryStatus.name: deliveryStatus
https://schema.org/deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

https://schema.org/parentTaxon.name: parentTaxon
https://schema.org/parentTaxon.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

https://schema.org/spatialCoverage.name: spatialCoverage
https://schema.org/spatialCoverage.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

https://schema.org/yield.name: yield
https://schema.org/yield.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

https://schema.org/sizeSystem.name: sizeSystem
https://schema.org/sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

https://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.name: countryOfOrigin
https://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.description:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

https://schema.org/openingHoursSpecifica.name: openingHoursSpecification
https://schema.org/openingHoursSpecifica.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

https://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.name: accountOverdraftLimit
https://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.description: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

https://schema.org/streetAddress.name: streetAddress
https://schema.org/streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

https://schema.org/acceptedOffer.name: acceptedOffer
https://schema.org/acceptedOffer.description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

https://schema.org/episode.name: episode
https://schema.org/episode.description: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

https://schema.org/isVariantOf.name: isVariantOf
https://schema.org/isVariantOf.description: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with [[ProductGroup]], this property can apply to any [[Product]] included in the group.

https://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.name: hasOfferCatalog
https://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

https://schema.org/titleEIDR.name: titleEIDR
https://schema.org/titleEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

https://schema.org/priceType.name: priceType
https://schema.org/priceType.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

https://schema.org/publishedOn.name: publishedOn
https://schema.org/publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

https://schema.org/hasHealthAspect.name: hasHealthAspect
https://schema.org/hasHealthAspect.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

https://schema.org/typeOfBed.name: typeOfBed
https://schema.org/typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

https://schema.org/firstPerformance.name: firstPerformance
https://schema.org/firstPerformance.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

https://schema.org/downvoteCount.name: downvoteCount
https://schema.org/downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

https://schema.org/sha256.name: sha256
https://schema.org/sha256.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'

https://schema.org/freeShippingThreshold.name: freeShippingThreshold
https://schema.org/freeShippingThreshold.description: A monetary value above which (or equal to) the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

https://schema.org/claimInterpreter.name: claimInterpreter
https://schema.org/claimInterpreter.description:
For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content
    sed to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

https://schema.org/spatial.name: spatial
https://schema.org/spatial.description:
The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties
(e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

https://schema.org/processorRequirements.name: processorRequirements
https://schema.org/processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

https://schema.org/game.name: game
https://schema.org/game.description: Video game which is played on this server.

https://schema.org/reviewedBy.name: reviewedBy
https://schema.org/reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

https://schema.org/clinicalPharmacology.name: clinicalPharmacology
https://schema.org/clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

https://schema.org/postOp.name: postOp
https://schema.org/postOp.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

https://schema.org/cookTime.name: cookTime
https://schema.org/cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/priceCurrency.name: priceCurrency
https://schema.org/priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.name: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

https://schema.org/commentCount.name: commentCount
https://schema.org/commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnFees.name: itemDefectReturnFees
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnFees.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

https://schema.org/isUnlabelledFallback.name: isUnlabelledFallback
https://schema.org/isUnlabelledFallback.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

https://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpe.name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
https://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpe.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

https://schema.org/algorithm.name: algorithm
https://schema.org/algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

https://schema.org/dropoffLocation.name: dropoffLocation
https://schema.org/dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

https://schema.org/usedToDiagnose.name: usedToDiagnose
https://schema.org/usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

https://schema.org/shippingRate.name: shippingRate
https://schema.org/shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

https://schema.org/healthPlanId.name: healthPlanId
https://schema.org/healthPlanId.description: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)

https://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.name: amountOfThisGood
https://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

https://schema.org/eventSchedule.name: eventSchedule
https://schema.org/eventSchedule.description:
Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of
      repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly
      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that
      is associated with a [[Schedule]] using this property should not have [[startDate]] or [[endDate]] properties. These are instead defined within the associated
      [[Schedule]], this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months
      or seasons.

https://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.name: broadcastChannelId
https://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

https://schema.org/seller.name: seller
https://schema.org/seller.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

https://schema.org/installUrl.name: installUrl
https://schema.org/installUrl.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

https://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatient.name: isAcceptingNewPatients
https://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatient.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

https://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.name: fuelEfficiency
https://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

https://schema.org/modifiedTime.name: modifiedTime
https://schema.org/modifiedTime.description: The date and time the reservation was modified.

https://schema.org/aspect.name: aspect
https://schema.org/aspect.description: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

https://schema.org/artEdition.name: artEdition
https://schema.org/artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

https://schema.org/preOp.name: preOp
https://schema.org/preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

https://schema.org/regionsAllowed.name: regionsAllowed
https://schema.org/regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

https://schema.org/eligibleRegion.name: eligibleRegion
https://schema.org/eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

https://schema.org/warrantyPromise.name: warrantyPromise
https://schema.org/warrantyPromise.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

https://schema.org/alumniOf.name: alumniOf
https://schema.org/alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

https://schema.org/shippingDetails.name: shippingDetails
https://schema.org/shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/childTaxon.name: childTaxon
https://schema.org/childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

https://schema.org/boardingGroup.name: boardingGroup
https://schema.org/boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

https://schema.org/upvoteCount.name: upvoteCount
https://schema.org/upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

https://schema.org/studyDesign.name: studyDesign
https://schema.org/studyDesign.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

https://schema.org/productGroupID.name: productGroupID
https://schema.org/productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

https://schema.org/afterMedia.name: afterMedia
https://schema.org/afterMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

https://schema.org/specialOpeningHoursSp.name: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
https://schema.org/specialOpeningHoursSp.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

https://schema.org/expires.name: expires
https://schema.org/expires.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

https://schema.org/termDuration.name: termDuration
https://schema.org/termDuration.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

https://schema.org/text.name: text
https://schema.org/text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/codeValue.name: codeValue
https://schema.org/codeValue.description: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

https://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGue.name: additionalNumberOfGuests
https://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGue.description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

https://schema.org/naics.name: naics
https://schema.org/naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

https://schema.org/missionCoveragePriori.name: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
https://schema.org/missionCoveragePriori.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

https://schema.org/bitrate.name: bitrate
https://schema.org/bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

https://schema.org/diversityStaffingRepo.name: diversityStaffingReport
https://schema.org/diversityStaffingRepo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

https://schema.org/priceSpecification.name: priceSpecification
https://schema.org/priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

https://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.name: arrivalPlatform
https://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

https://schema.org/isPartOfBioChemEntity.name: isPartOfBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/isPartOfBioChemEntity.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

https://schema.org/isicV4.name: isicV4
https://schema.org/isicV4.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

https://schema.org/gameItem.name: gameItem
https://schema.org/gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

https://schema.org/postOfficeBoxNumber.name: postOfficeBoxNumber
https://schema.org/postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

https://schema.org/sodiumContent.name: sodiumContent
https://schema.org/sodiumContent.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

https://schema.org/passengerPriorityStat.name: passengerPriorityStatus
https://schema.org/passengerPriorityStat.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

https://schema.org/merchantReturnDays.name: merchantReturnDays
https://schema.org/merchantReturnDays.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnShipp.name: itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnShipp.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

https://schema.org/geoRadius.name: geoRadius
https://schema.org/geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

https://schema.org/price.name: price
https://schema.org/price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Tradings Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

https://schema.org/specialCommitments.name: specialCommitments
https://schema.org/specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

https://schema.org/nonEqual.name: nonEqual
https://schema.org/nonEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

https://schema.org/sourceOrganization.name: sourceOrganization
https://schema.org/sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

https://schema.org/returnPolicyCountry.name: returnPolicyCountry
https://schema.org/returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent too.

https://schema.org/cashBack.name: cashBack
https://schema.org/cashBack.description: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

https://schema.org/businessDays.name: businessDays
https://schema.org/businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

https://schema.org/volumeNumber.name: volumeNumber
https://schema.org/volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

https://schema.org/knowsAbout.name: knowsAbout
https://schema.org/knowsAbout.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

https://schema.org/observedNode.name: observedNode
https://schema.org/observedNode.description: The observedNode of an [[Observation]], often a [[StatisticalPopulation]].

https://schema.org/schemaVersion.name: schemaVersion
https://schema.org/schemaVersion.description:
Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to
    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

https://schema.org/cvdNumVentUse.name: cvdNumVentUse
https://schema.org/cvdNumVentUse.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

https://schema.org/recordedAs.name: recordedAs
https://schema.org/recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

https://schema.org/membershipNumber.name: membershipNumber
https://schema.org/membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

https://schema.org/torque.name: torque
https://schema.org/torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/partOfInvoice.name: partOfInvoice
https://schema.org/partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

https://schema.org/competitor.name: competitor
https://schema.org/competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

https://schema.org/applicationDeadline.name: applicationDeadline
https://schema.org/applicationDeadline.description: The date at which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

https://schema.org/steeringPosition.name: steeringPosition
https://schema.org/steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

https://schema.org/partOfTVSeries.name: partOfTVSeries
https://schema.org/partOfTVSeries.description: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

https://schema.org/attendee.name: attendee
https://schema.org/attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

https://schema.org/potentialUse.name: potentialUse
https://schema.org/potentialUse.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

https://schema.org/step.name: step
https://schema.org/step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

https://schema.org/workload.name: workload
https://schema.org/workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

https://schema.org/audience.name: audience
https://schema.org/audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

https://schema.org/loser.name: loser
https://schema.org/loser.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

https://schema.org/wheelbase.name: wheelbase
https://schema.org/wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet

https://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.name: accessibilityFeature
https://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility ([WebSchemas wiki lists possible values](http://www.w3.org/wiki/WebSchemas/Accessibility)).

https://schema.org/inLanguage.name: inLanguage
https://schema.org/inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

https://schema.org/opens.name: opens
https://schema.org/opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

https://schema.org/numberOfPlayers.name: numberOfPlayers
https://schema.org/numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

https://schema.org/geoWithin.name: geoWithin
https://schema.org/geoWithin.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/experienceRequirement.name: experienceRequirements
https://schema.org/experienceRequirement.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

https://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCat.name: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
https://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCat.description: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

https://schema.org/advanceBookingRequire.name: advanceBookingRequirement
https://schema.org/advanceBookingRequire.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

https://schema.org/salaryCurrency.name: salaryCurrency
https://schema.org/salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) ) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

https://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.name: breastfeedingWarning
https://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

https://schema.org/browserRequirements.name: browserRequirements
https://schema.org/browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

https://schema.org/agent.name: agent
https://schema.org/agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. *John* wrote a book.

https://schema.org/stageAsNumber.name: stageAsNumber
https://schema.org/stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

https://schema.org/valueMaxLength.name: valueMaxLength
https://schema.org/valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

https://schema.org/blogPost.name: blogPost
https://schema.org/blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

https://schema.org/safetyConsideration.name: safetyConsideration
https://schema.org/safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

https://schema.org/characterName.name: characterName
https://schema.org/characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

https://schema.org/temporal.name: temporal
https://schema.org/temporal.description:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

https://schema.org/insertion.name: insertion
https://schema.org/insertion.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

https://schema.org/typicalCreditsPerTerm.name: typicalCreditsPerTerm
https://schema.org/typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

https://schema.org/sportsEvent.name: sportsEvent
https://schema.org/sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

https://schema.org/geoIntersects.name: geoIntersects
https://schema.org/geoIntersects.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/positiveNotes.name: positiveNotes
https://schema.org/positiveNotes.description: Indicates, in the context of a [[Review]] (e.g. framed as 'pro' vs 'con' considerations), positive considerations - either as unstructured text, or a list.

https://schema.org/knows.name: knows
https://schema.org/knows.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

https://schema.org/genre.name: genre
https://schema.org/genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

https://schema.org/pickupLocation.name: pickupLocation
https://schema.org/pickupLocation.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

https://schema.org/fuelConsumption.name: fuelConsumption
https://schema.org/fuelConsumption.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

https://schema.org/reservationStatus.name: reservationStatus
https://schema.org/reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

https://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.name: increasesRiskOf
https://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

https://schema.org/occupationLocation.name: occupationLocation
https://schema.org/occupationLocation.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

https://schema.org/weight.name: weight
https://schema.org/weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

https://schema.org/foodEvent.name: foodEvent
https://schema.org/foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

https://schema.org/language.name: language
https://schema.org/language.description: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

https://schema.org/regionDrained.name: regionDrained
https://schema.org/regionDrained.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

https://schema.org/actor.name: actor
https://schema.org/actor.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/serviceAudience.name: serviceAudience
https://schema.org/serviceAudience.description: The audience eligible for this service.

https://schema.org/includedComposition.name: includedComposition
https://schema.org/includedComposition.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

https://schema.org/legislationDateVersio.name: legislationDateVersion
https://schema.org/legislationDateVersio.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g. : when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

https://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPol.name: actionableFeedbackPolicy
https://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPol.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

https://schema.org/minValue.name: minValue
https://schema.org/minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

https://schema.org/proprietaryName.name: proprietaryName
https://schema.org/proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

https://schema.org/sizeGroup.name: sizeGroup
https://schema.org/sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular"

https://schema.org/dayOfWeek.name: dayOfWeek
https://schema.org/dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

https://schema.org/workExample.name: workExample
https://schema.org/workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

https://schema.org/estimatedFlightDurati.name: estimatedFlightDuration
https://schema.org/estimatedFlightDurati.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

https://schema.org/foundingLocation.name: foundingLocation
https://schema.org/foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

https://schema.org/referenceQuantity.name: referenceQuantity
https://schema.org/referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

https://schema.org/materialExtent.name: materialExtent
https://schema.org/materialExtent.description: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

https://schema.org/departureTerminal.name: departureTerminal
https://schema.org/departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

https://schema.org/earlyPrepaymentPenalt.name: earlyPrepaymentPenalty
https://schema.org/earlyPrepaymentPenalt.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

https://schema.org/experienceInPlaceOfEd.name: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
https://schema.org/experienceInPlaceOfEd.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

https://schema.org/serviceType.name: serviceType
https://schema.org/serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

https://schema.org/iupacName.name: iupacName
https://schema.org/iupacName.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

https://schema.org/returnPolicySeasonalO.name: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
https://schema.org/returnPolicySeasonalO.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

https://schema.org/availableDeliveryMeth.name: availableDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/availableDeliveryMeth.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

https://schema.org/gamePlatform.name: gamePlatform
https://schema.org/gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

https://schema.org/monthsOfExperience.name: monthsOfExperience
https://schema.org/monthsOfExperience.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

https://schema.org/distinguishingSign.name: distinguishingSign
https://schema.org/distinguishingSign.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

https://schema.org/resultReview.name: resultReview
https://schema.org/resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

https://schema.org/acceptsReservations.name: acceptsReservations
https://schema.org/acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

https://schema.org/infectiousAgent.name: infectiousAgent
https://schema.org/infectiousAgent.description: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

https://schema.org/geographicArea.name: geographicArea
https://schema.org/geographicArea.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

https://schema.org/numberOfCredits.name: numberOfCredits
https://schema.org/numberOfCredits.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

https://schema.org/biologicalRole.name: biologicalRole
https://schema.org/biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

https://schema.org/httpMethod.name: httpMethod
https://schema.org/httpMethod.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

https://schema.org/arrivalAirport.name: arrivalAirport
https://schema.org/arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

https://schema.org/processingTime.name: processingTime
https://schema.org/processingTime.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

https://schema.org/dropoffTime.name: dropoffTime
https://schema.org/dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

https://schema.org/coursePrerequisites.name: coursePrerequisites
https://schema.org/coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

https://schema.org/printEdition.name: printEdition
https://schema.org/printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

https://schema.org/procedure.name: procedure
https://schema.org/procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

https://schema.org/timeOfDay.name: timeOfDay
https://schema.org/timeOfDay.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

https://schema.org/verificationFactCheck.name: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
https://schema.org/verificationFactCheck.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

https://schema.org/defaultValue.name: defaultValue
https://schema.org/defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

https://schema.org/collectionSize.name: collectionSize
https://schema.org/collectionSize.description: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

https://schema.org/recipeCuisine.name: recipeCuisine
https://schema.org/recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

https://schema.org/free.name: free
https://schema.org/free.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

https://schema.org/overdosage.name: overdosage
https://schema.org/overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

https://schema.org/purchaseDate.name: purchaseDate
https://schema.org/purchaseDate.description: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

https://schema.org/connectedTo.name: connectedTo
https://schema.org/connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

https://schema.org/legislationPassedBy.name: legislationPassedBy
https://schema.org/legislationPassedBy.description: The person or organization that originally passed or made the law : typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

https://schema.org/artform.name: artform
https://schema.org/artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

https://schema.org/countriesNotSupported.name: countriesNotSupported
https://schema.org/countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

https://schema.org/targetName.name: targetName
https://schema.org/targetName.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/honorificPrefix.name: honorificPrefix
https://schema.org/honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

https://schema.org/interpretedAsClaim.name: interpretedAsClaim
https://schema.org/interpretedAsClaim.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

https://schema.org/layoutImage.name: layoutImage
https://schema.org/layoutImage.description: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

https://schema.org/broker.name: broker
https://schema.org/broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

https://schema.org/gtin14.name: gtin14
https://schema.org/gtin14.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/pathophysiology.name: pathophysiology
https://schema.org/pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

https://schema.org/noBylinesPolicy.name: noBylinesPolicy
https://schema.org/noBylinesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

https://schema.org/interactionService.name: interactionService
https://schema.org/interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

https://schema.org/numTracks.name: numTracks
https://schema.org/numTracks.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

https://schema.org/homeLocation.name: homeLocation
https://schema.org/homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

https://schema.org/mediaAuthenticityCate.name: mediaAuthenticityCategory
https://schema.org/mediaAuthenticityCate.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

https://schema.org/availableStrength.name: availableStrength
https://schema.org/availableStrength.description: An available dosage strength for the drug.

https://schema.org/bookingAgent.name: bookingAgent
https://schema.org/bookingAgent.description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

https://schema.org/author.name: author
https://schema.org/author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

https://schema.org/baseSalary.name: baseSalary
https://schema.org/baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

https://schema.org/applicableLocation.name: applicableLocation
https://schema.org/applicableLocation.description: The location in which the status applies.

https://schema.org/recipeIngredient.name: recipeIngredient
https://schema.org/recipeIngredient.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

https://schema.org/antagonist.name: antagonist
https://schema.org/antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

https://schema.org/orderDelivery.name: orderDelivery
https://schema.org/orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

https://schema.org/itemCondition.name: itemCondition
https://schema.org/itemCondition.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

https://schema.org/announcementLocation.name: announcementLocation
https://schema.org/announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

https://schema.org/lender.name: lender
https://schema.org/lender.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

https://schema.org/parentOrganization.name: parentOrganization
https://schema.org/parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

https://schema.org/guidelineDate.name: guidelineDate
https://schema.org/guidelineDate.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

https://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.name: accountMinimumInflow
https://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.description: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

https://schema.org/signDetected.name: signDetected
https://schema.org/signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

https://schema.org/deathPlace.name: deathPlace
https://schema.org/deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

https://schema.org/servicePhone.name: servicePhone
https://schema.org/servicePhone.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

https://schema.org/arterialBranch.name: arterialBranch
https://schema.org/arterialBranch.description: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

https://schema.org/numberOfAccommodation.name: numberOfAccommodationUnits
https://schema.org/numberOfAccommodation.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

https://schema.org/athlete.name: athlete
https://schema.org/athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

https://schema.org/trainName.name: trainName
https://schema.org/trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

https://schema.org/articleBody.name: articleBody
https://schema.org/articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

https://schema.org/procedureType.name: procedureType
https://schema.org/procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

https://schema.org/departureBusStop.name: departureBusStop
https://schema.org/departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

https://schema.org/colorist.name: colorist
https://schema.org/colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

https://schema.org/priceComponentType.name: priceComponentType
https://schema.org/priceComponentType.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

https://schema.org/geoCrosses.name: geoCrosses
https://schema.org/geoCrosses.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/albumReleaseType.name: albumReleaseType
https://schema.org/albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

https://schema.org/creator.name: creator
https://schema.org/creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/copyrightYear.name: copyrightYear
https://schema.org/copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

https://schema.org/costPerUnit.name: costPerUnit
https://schema.org/costPerUnit.description: The cost per unit of the drug.

https://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.name: arrivalBusStop
https://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.name: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.description: Whether The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

https://schema.org/fileFormat.name: fileFormat
https://schema.org/fileFormat.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

https://schema.org/gtin13.name: gtin13
https://schema.org/gtin13.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/suggestedMinAge.name: suggestedMinAge
https://schema.org/suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

https://schema.org/loanType.name: loanType
https://schema.org/loanType.description: The type of a loan or credit.

https://schema.org/exercisePlan.name: exercisePlan
https://schema.org/exercisePlan.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

https://schema.org/isResizable.name: isResizable
https://schema.org/isResizable.description: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

https://schema.org/abridged.name: abridged
https://schema.org/abridged.description: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

https://schema.org/mechanismOfAction.name: mechanismOfAction
https://schema.org/mechanismOfAction.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

https://schema.org/stage.name: stage
https://schema.org/stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

https://schema.org/maps.name: maps
https://schema.org/maps.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/subStageSuffix.name: subStageSuffix
https://schema.org/subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

https://schema.org/option.name: option
https://schema.org/option.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

https://schema.org/hasRepresentation.name: hasRepresentation
https://schema.org/hasRepresentation.description: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

https://schema.org/lyricist.name: lyricist
https://schema.org/lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

https://schema.org/addOn.name: addOn
https://schema.org/addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

https://schema.org/passengerSequenceNumb.name: passengerSequenceNumber
https://schema.org/passengerSequenceNumb.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

https://schema.org/postalCodeBegin.name: postalCodeBegin
https://schema.org/postalCodeBegin.description: First postal code in a range (included).

https://schema.org/dateRead.name: dateRead
https://schema.org/dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

https://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.name: hasDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

https://schema.org/duns.name: duns
https://schema.org/duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

https://schema.org/costCurrency.name: costCurrency
https://schema.org/costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

https://schema.org/loanMortgageMandateAm.name: loanMortgageMandateAmount
https://schema.org/loanMortgageMandateAm.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

https://schema.org/loanPaymentAmount.name: loanPaymentAmount
https://schema.org/loanPaymentAmount.description: The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

https://schema.org/numberOfRooms.name: numberOfRooms
https://schema.org/numberOfRooms.description:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

https://schema.org/occupancy.name: occupancy
https://schema.org/occupancy.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

https://schema.org/performer.name: performer
https://schema.org/performer.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

https://schema.org/significantLinks.name: significantLinks
https://schema.org/significantLinks.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

https://schema.org/pageEnd.name: pageEnd
https://schema.org/pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

https://schema.org/awards.name: awards
https://schema.org/awards.description: Awards won by or for this item.

https://schema.org/learningResourceType.name: learningResourceType
https://schema.org/learningResourceType.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

https://schema.org/broadcastSubChannel.name: broadcastSubChannel
https://schema.org/broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

https://schema.org/lesserOrEqual.name: lesserOrEqual
https://schema.org/lesserOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

https://schema.org/suggestedMeasurement.name: suggestedMeasurement
https://schema.org/suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

https://schema.org/relatedStructure.name: relatedStructure
https://schema.org/relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

https://schema.org/issuedBy.name: issuedBy
https://schema.org/issuedBy.description: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.
